# BROWSER-replies.md - IH Notification & Reply Patterns

## S 1. Extract Notifications

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var b = document.querySelector('#onetrust-accept-btn-handler'); if (b) b.click(); var months = {JAN:'01',FEB:'02',MAR:'03',APR:'04',MAY:'05',JUN:'06',JUL:'07',AUG:'08',SEP:'09',OCT:'10',NOV:'11',DEC:'12'}; var items = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.user-notification')); var result = items.slice(0, 10).map(function(item) { var link = item.querySelector('a[href*=\"/post/\"]') || item.querySelector('a[href*=\"/product/\"]'); var text = item.innerText; var isReply = text.toLowerCase().includes('replied to your comment') || text.toLowerCase().includes('replied to your post'); var url = link ? link.href : null; var commentId = url ? (url.match(/commentId=([^&]+)/) || [])[1] || '' : ''; var dateMatch = text.match(/([A-Z]{3})\\s+(\\d{1,2})\\s+(\\d{4})/); var dateKey = dateMatch ? dateMatch[3] + '-' + (months[dateMatch[1]] || '00') + '-' + dateMatch[2].padStart(2, '0') : ''; return { url: url, commentId: commentId, dateKey: dateKey, trackingKey: commentId + '_' + dateKey, preview: text.substring(0, 200), isReplyToUs: isReply }; }).filter(function(n) { return n.isReplyToUs && n.url; }); return { total: items.length, replies: result.length, items: result }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

⚠️ Use `trackingKey` (not raw URL) for grep pre-check against `replied_notifications.txt`.

## S 3. Click Reply Button

Clicks reply on a specific author's comment. Checks for duplicate first.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var selected = document.querySelector('.comment--selected'); if (selected) { var selectedLi = selected.closest('li'); if (selectedLi) { var allComments = selectedLi.querySelectorAll('.comment'); var ourReply = Array.from(allComments).some(function(c) { return c !== selected && c.innerText.includes('{{handle}}'); }); if (ourReply) return { skipped: true, reason: 'already_replied' }; } } var footers = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.comment__footer')); var targetFooter = footers.find(function(f) { return f.innerText.includes(window.__data.author); }); if (!targetFooter) return { error: 'target_comment_not_found' }; var replyButton = targetFooter.querySelector('.footer__action--reply'); if (!replyButton) return { error: 'reply_button_not_found' }; replyButton.click(); return { success: true, clicked: 'reply_button' }; }", "data": {"author": "TARGET_AUTHOR_NAME"}}
ENDJSON
```

## S 4. Type + Submit Reply (2 evaluates: type then submit+verify)

Call 1.5s after clicking reply (embedded via Promise-based wait). IH uses plain `textarea` (not TipTap). TipTap fallback kept for edge cases.

- 🚨 NEVER combine text insertion + submit click in one evaluate (button stays disabled until next tick)

```bash
# Evaluate 1: Wait 1.5s for reply box + type text ONLY
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); var commentBox = document.querySelector('.comment-box--focused'); if (!commentBox) return { error: 'comment_box_did_not_appear' }; var textarea = commentBox.querySelector('textarea'); var editor = commentBox.querySelector('.tiptap.ProseMirror'); if (textarea) { textarea.focus(); textarea.value = window.__data.text; textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); return { inserted: true, textLen: textarea.value.length, type: 'textarea' }; } else if (editor) { editor.focus(); document.execCommand('selectAll', false, null); document.execCommand('delete', false, null); document.execCommand('insertText', false, window.__data.text); editor.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('input', { data: window.__data.text, inputType: 'insertText', bubbles: true })); return { inserted: true, textLen: editor.innerText.length, type: 'tiptap' }; } else { return { error: 'no_editor_found' }; } }", "data": {"text": "YOUR_REPLY_HERE"}}
ENDJSON
```

```bash
# Evaluate 2: Wait 500ms, submit, wait 4s, verify (scoped then fallback)
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { var beforeCount = document.querySelectorAll('.comment').length; await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var commentBox = document.querySelector('.comment-box--focused') || document.querySelector('.comment-box'); if (!commentBox) return { error: 'comment_box_not_found' }; var submitBtn = commentBox.querySelector('.comment-box__save-button'); if (!submitBtn) return { error: 'submit_button_not_found' }; if (submitBtn.disabled) return { error: 'submit_still_disabled' }; submitBtn.click(); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 4000)); var selected = document.querySelector('.comment--selected'); var verified = false; if (selected) { var selectedLi = selected.closest('li'); if (selectedLi) { var allComments = selectedLi.querySelectorAll('.comment'); verified = Array.from(allComments).some(function(c) { return c !== selected && c.innerText.includes('{{handle}}'); }); } } var afterCount = document.querySelectorAll('.comment').length; if (!verified && afterCount > beforeCount) verified = true; return { success: true, verified: verified }; }"}
ENDJSON
```
